NAMC Tree — National Ayurveda Morbidity Codes Interactive Tree

This project was developed and published by Namaste Ayush Portal
as a free, open-access reference tool for Ayurveda practitioners,
researchers, educators, and students worldwide.

The underlying morbidity code data (NAMC codes, Sanskrit terms,
Devanāgarī transliterations, and clinical definitions) is based on
the National Ayurveda Morbidity Codes developed under the Ministry
of AYUSH, Government of India. All such data remains the property
of its respective originators and is reproduced here for educational
and research purposes.

